  "texts": [
    "Post-hoc comparisons using the Tukey HSD test indicated that the mean score for AI-Assisted Code Refiners (M = 8.35, SD = 3.22) was significantly higher than AI-Reliant Code Generators (M = 5.5, SD = 3.49), p =.008.",
    "These results may suggest that students with higher previous knowledge more tend to behave like AI-Assisted Code Refiners.",
    "A total of 143 students in the 1st session, 146 students in the 2nd session, and 140 students in the 3rd session both took the post-test and uploaded their ChatGPT conversation histories.",
    "The post-test scores (out of 2 points) for each session based on AI interaction profiles are presented in Table 5.",
    "For the 1st session, the Shapiro-Wilk test indicated that the AI-Reliant Code Generators showed a small deviation from normality, W (45) = 0.949, p =.045, while other profiles did not (all p values > 0.17)."
